{
  "info": {
    "name": "9.6 \u2014 TokenVault Regression (STAGE)",
    "description": "Release 9.6 STAGE \u2014 Testmo folder TokenVault (13 cases).\n\nImport env `9.6 TokenVault Regression STAGE`.\nAuth client: WellfitUnifiedPaymentsAPI (has TokenVault Read/Write + Payments V2).\n\nRunnable without hardware: TC01\u2013TC04, TC08\u2013TC12.\nPARKED (physical CP lane): TC05\u2013TC07, TC13.\n\nHosts:\n- Payments {{URL}} = https://stage-platform.wellfit.com/payments\n- TokenVault {{TokenVaultAPI}} = https://stage-platform.wellfit.com/tokenvault\n\nProcessorTokens: TokenVault.dbo.PaymentTokens numeric only (see CNP docs).\nCase 167997 had empty Testmo body \u2014 scaffolded from TokenVault API collection.\n\n**CP note:** Needs QA lead support for physical lane/cardToken. Simulator 9999 not enough.\nPreferred: use unified collection `Regression - STAGE` \u2192 folder TokenVault.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "00. Auth (run first)",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST Authenticate Payment (STAGE)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{URL}}/authenticate",
            "description": "STAGE payments authenticate. Saves Payment-Bearer-Token (UnifiedPayments has TokenVault Read/Write).",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"{{paymentsUsername}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{paymentsPassword}}\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('HTTP 200', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.eql(200));",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('bearerToken present', () => pm.expect(j.bearerToken).to.be.ok);",
                  "pm.environment.set('Payment-Bearer-Token', j.bearerToken);",
                  "console.log('token saved');"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "TC01. Ensure CNP V1 endpoint is able to make a successful payment with processor token",
      "description": "Case 167990. process-card with numeric ProcessorToken. Expect 200 + PaymentTypeMethod=2.\nDB: TokenVault.dbo.PaymentTokens (not Platform).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST process-card \u2014 processor token",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{Payment-Bearer-Token}}"
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{URL}}/credit-card/process-card",
            "description": "Use {{tokenVisa}} numeric ProcessorToken. No cvv/zip.",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"amount\": 11.01,\n  \"expirationDate\": \"{{expirationDate}}\",\n  \"network\": \"VI\",\n  \"orderId\": \"{{orderId}}\",\n  \"payFacFee\": 0,\n  \"subMerchantId\": \"{{subMerchantId}}\",\n  \"token\": \"{{tokenVisa}}\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const orderId = 'R96-TV-' + Date.now().toString().slice(-10);",
                  "pm.environment.set('orderId', orderId);",
                  "console.log('orderId=' + orderId);"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('HTTP 200', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.eql(200));",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "const txn = j.transactionId || j.TransactionId || (j.response && j.response.transactionId);",
                  "pm.test('transactionId present', () => pm.expect(txn).to.be.ok);",
                  "pm.environment.set('lastTransactionId', String(txn));",
                  "console.log('lastTransactionId=' + txn);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "SQL \u2014 Payments PaymentTypeMethod=2 (Send \u2192 Visualize)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "https://postman-echo.com/get",
            "description": "Platform DB. Expect PaymentTypeMethod = 2.",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "SELECT Id, TransactionId, Amount, PaymentTypeMethod, OrderId, TimeStamp\nFROM [Payments].[Payments]\nWHERE TransactionId = '{{lastTransactionId}}';\n-- Expect PaymentTypeMethod = 2",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "text"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const id = pm.environment.get('lastTransactionId') || '';",
                  "if (!id) { pm.test('id present', () => pm.expect.fail('Empty \u2014 run prior API first')); return; }",
                  "let sql = \"SELECT Id, TransactionId, Amount, PaymentTypeMethod, OrderId, TimeStamp\\nFROM [Payments].[Payments]\\nWHERE TransactionId = '{id}';\\n-- Expect PaymentTypeMethod = 2\";",
                  "sql = sql.replace('{id}', id);",
                  "console.log(sql);",
                  "pm.visualizer.set(`<h3>Copy SQL \u2192 Platform DB</h3><pre style=\"white-space:pre-wrap;background:#1e1e1e;color:#ddd;padding:12px;\">${sql}</pre><p>Id: ${id}</p>`, {sql, id});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "TC02. Ensure CNP V1 endpoint is able to make a successful payment with token GUID",
      "description": "Case 167991. add-token \u2192 GUID \u2192 process-card with GUID in token.\nIf STAGE returns Token was not found, note as product/env gap (same as WPAC* issue).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST add-token \u2014 create Wellfit GUID",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{Payment-Bearer-Token}}"
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{TokenVaultAPI}}/add-token",
            "description": "Creates TokenVault GUID from processorToken. Saves wellfitTokenGuid.",
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"id\": \"{{$guid}}\",\n  \"processorToken\": \"{{tokenVisa}}\",\n  \"cardLastFour\": \"{{cardLastFourVisa}}\",\n  \"cardBrand\": \"VISA\",\n  \"cardExpirationMonth\": 12,\n  \"cardExpirationYear\": 2034,\n  \"cardZipCode\": \"01803\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "response": [],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('HTTP 2xx', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.be.within(200, 299));",
                  "const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "const id = j.id || j.Id || j.tokenId || j.TokenId;",
                  "pm.test('GUID present', () => pm.expect(id).to.be.ok);",
                  "pm.environment.set('wellfitTokenGuid', String(id));",
                  "console.log('wellfitTokenGuid=' + id);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
